portfolio.name: UCF Parking Agent
portfolio.description: is a hackathon project created in Knight Hack hosted at University of Central Florida, Orlando. It predicts and shows what is the current number of occupancy in a certain parking garage at UCF. This was built in Dialogflow and Nodejs. This was built by Terrell Ibanez, Cole Orlando, Blake Wyatt and myself.

portfolio.name: Nayoshi Github Pages
portfolio.description: My awesome website is written by myself without the use of templates or bootstraps. I created this website to challenge myself how far I can get with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Inspiration from Japan and Dark Florida Weather.

portfolio.name: Mythic GUI
portfolio.description: Mythic GUI is a Minecraft spigot plugin, created for the purpose of selling to the public. It was a supplement to a popular spigot plugin called Mythic Mobs. It was made to make it easier for developers/users of the plugin to summon items without typing a long winded string of commands

portfolio.name: Christmas Cracker
portfolio.description: Christmas Cracker is a Minecraft spigot plugin. It was created to add christmas crackers in to the game. A christmas cracker is an object that resemble a peppermint, which you can pulled and there will gifts inside. It originated in England and popularized by Runescape.

portfolio.name: Mass Messaging Discord Bot
portfolio.description: The discord bot is written in nodejs, and express and express-handlebars as the website server. The discord bot creates a website where you can select which server you want to target, and choose a role for which to ignore, and a channel where you could keep all the logs. Then you can type in a message, and then it will allow it to send a personal message (Direct Message or DM) to a person using the bot. It will do it as slowly as possible to prevent being rate-limited. It has been discontinued and disabled because of discovery of Discord TOS, and this can be considered as API-abuse.

portfolio.name: Bee Movie Discord Bot
portfolio.description: A silly discord bot which allows a bot to post, line by line, every single word in the Bee Movie(2007). It was mostly a test to determine which open-source website allow lenient error code paste hosting. Pastebin is the winner, allowing it to store more the 1.2k lines of dialogue and monologue.
